FBIS4-6628 "dreas078_n_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 Vietnam New MIA Search, Interviews Begin 21 Apr New MIA Search, Interviews Begin 21 Apr BK2204111494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 22 Apr 94 BK2204111494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam English BFN [Text] A new search for missing in action [MIA] from the Vietnam war began on Thursday with the participation of more than 100 American specialists. It is the second biggest search since the lifting of the United States trade embargo. They will conduct interviews of local people, and undertake excavations in 15 provinces and the three large cities of Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh City, and Haiphong. Lieutenant Colonel John Cray, chief of the United States MIA Bureau in Hanoi, said that over the past six weeks, American specialists visited 10 prisons but did not find any evidence of the Americans detained after the war.
